{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"The conversation history passed to the LLM is trimmed to the most recent 10 messages when the full history exceeds the context window.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Failure boundary is module handoff: history-trimming logic must be correctly applied in the request actually sent by the orchestrator to the LLM client. A pure Unit test of a trim helper can pass while integration code still sends untrimmed history (wrong mapper/field/path). No real OS/network/subprocess is required, and correctness does not depend on real model output.","test_description":"Wire chat handler + prompt builder + LLM client adapter with a stub LLM endpoint that records payloads. Send >10-message history and assert outbound LLM payload contains exactly the most recent 10 messages in order.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.35,"Integration":0.6,"System":0.03,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"The generated response addresses the customer's question rather than producing a generic or off-topic reply.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"This is output-quality correctness of the model itself. Deterministic stubs always return fixture-good answers and cannot expose real off-topic/generic generations. Single model judgment step, so Agentic (not Workflow). Lower-level miss-proof: Integration can verify routing/retries but not semantic relevance.","test_description":"Run real LLM calls on a fixed evaluation set of customer questions and score relevance/answerability (rubric or pairwise judge). Fail if off-topic/generic rate exceeds threshold.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0,"Integration":0.05,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.85,"Workflow":0.05}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"The tone re-check correctly identifies when a response is too formal for a casual-tier customer and triggers regeneration.","minimum_level":"Workflow","justification":"Behavior explicitly spans multiple agentic decisions in sequence: initial generation -> tone judgment ('too formal') -> regeneration trigger. Mocking either model step can hide real failures in tone identification or in decision-to-regenerate coupling. Grounding evidence: 're-prompts the LLM if the initial response is flagged...' and behavior requires both identification and trigger.","test_description":"Execute end-to-end with real LLM tone-check path for casual-tier prompts designed to elicit formal first drafts. Assert run includes: initial draft, tone flag=true, regeneration call issued, and final delivered response comes from regenerated draft.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0,"Integration":0.04,"System":0.03,"Agentic":0.33,"Workflow":0.6}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"The full exchange (user message, generated response, any regenerations) is persisted to the database with correct timestamps.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Primary failure is local module wiring/state propagation into persistence (chat service + regeneration flow + repository + timestamp assignment). Real external infra is not required if using local test DB and controlled clock. Lower-level miss-proof: Unit tests of repository serializer can pass while orchestrator omits regeneration records or writes wrong event ordering.","test_description":"Run handler with stubbed LLM outputs that force one regeneration; use test DB and fixed/injected clock. Assert persisted records include user message, first draft, regenerated draft, final selection, and correct per-event timestamps/order.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.2,"Integration":0.72,"System":0.06,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"When the tone check triggers regeneration, the second response replaces the first — the customer never sees the rejected draft.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Behavior text is conditional on trigger already occurring ('When the tone check triggers regeneration'), so this test targets orchestration/output handoff, not model decision quality. Integration is enough to catch real failure where draft-1 leaks through delivery channel while storage/internal state updates to draft-2. Rejected higher level: Agentic is disqualified by the preconditioned wording, which does not require validating whether the model should have triggered.","test_description":"With tone-check result forced true (or controlled fixture path), execute request through response composer/delivery module and assert only regenerated text is returned to customer-facing payload/stream; rejected draft may exist in logs but never in customer output.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.18,"Integration":0.7,"System":0.07,"Agentic":0.05,"Workflow":0}}]}
